        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 6:03PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 603 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking an area of strong
thunderstorms near Livingston, moving north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Livingston, Big Timber, Clyde Park, Springdale, Pine Creek, Mc
Leod and Emigrant.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
